<br>
 Now, about soloing. After trying all the pets over and over again , yes even that pathetic fire pet, I have come to the conclusion that even if your water pet isn't behind the monster backstabbing it's still the best solo pet for most situtations  The air pet is good cause of it's high dex and better ac, but it's average damage is less then the water pet.  Testing both pets against the same type of monsters you will find that after each battle the air pet has less hitpoints and that the battle it's has lasted longer then with the water pet.  Why you ask? Well the water pets average damage is higher, plus he casts a decent nuke a lot.  Plus that regen they get is awesome.<br>
<br>
 Ok, so if you are wondering which monsters I have tested teh pets against, here is a list, and all of which I have found the water pet to be better against overall.<br>
Seafuries<br>
Elementals in the Hole<br>
Everything in The Grey<br>
Reverants in SD<br>
Dryads<br>
Rockhoppers<br>
Fish in Kedge<br>
Giants in Kael<br>
Giants in GD<br>
<br>
I am sure there is more but I can't think of them right now.  Now against the Elementals in the hole and Dryads.  I did find that the water pet does the best job against these creatures but went with a diffrent pet in the end due to other  reasons.  I had to use the Earth pet for his root against the elementals cause they tend to run and I have to waste mana for a nuke at the end to stop them.  I used the air pet against the Dryads because I hope his stun with stop some of the more annoying things about them like the dots and the roots. <br>
<br>
 Are all the pets useful(maybe even the fire if we can ever figure it out someday)?  Yes.  Is the water pet useless at soloing? NO.  Should you just sit here and take my word or the word of these other people? Hell no. Get the pet yourself and try it out.<br>
<br>
And tang, yes you are correct about the fact that it would have to be the 54 water pet that you witnessed.  Now, think about the other things I said.  Just because you are correct that it's the 54 water pet doesn't mean you know what the hell was going on when you watched it. Maybe the pet was slowed, or not BOed, or fighting against a mob that really out leveled it, or just had one of those bad melee rounds that all pets have from time to time.  Did you sit there and watch the pet for more then 15 or 20 min?  Did you ask yourself why he is usuing the water pet if it's so patheticly bad?  My same statement still applies. Wait til you get it and til you use it before you cast judgement and try to tell other people about it.  And please try and not be bias.  If after you get hte pet and use it for a good amount of time, you still feel the same way, well more power to you.<br>
